# cell-id-mapper

Cross-reference cancer cell line identifiers across **DepMap**, **GDSC (COSMIC)**, and **Sanger (Cell Model Passports)** databases.

If you've ever stared at a spreadsheet wondering whether "A549" in your GDSC drug response data is the same cell line as `ACH-000024` in your DepMap CRISPR screen, this tool is for you.

## Why

Three major cancer genomics resources use three different ID systems for the same cell lines. Manually reconciling them is tedious and error-prone. This package gives you a single function call to translate between them.

## Quick start

```bash
pip install cell-id-mapper
```

### Command line

```bash
# Look up by any identifier
cell-id-mapper lookup A549
cell-id-mapper lookup ACH-000024
cell-id-mapper lookup 905952          # COSMIC ID

# Fuzzy search
cell-id-mapper search "MCF"

# Convert between ID types
cell-id-mapper convert A549 --from name --to cosmic

# List all cell lines of a given lineage
cell-id-mapper lineage Breast

# Coverage statistics
cell-id-mapper stats
```

### Python API

```python
from cell_id_mapper import load_mapper

mapper = load_mapper()

# Exact lookups
cl = mapper.from_name("A549")
print(cl.depmap_id)   # ACH-000024
print(cl.cosmic_id)   # 905952
print(cl.sanger_id)   # SIDM000218
print(cl.lineage)     # Lung

# Convenience methods
mapper.ach_to_cosmic("ACH-000024")     # "905952"
mapper.name_to_ach("A549")             # "ACH-000024"
mapper.cosmic_to_name("905952")        # "A549"

# Fuzzy search
hits = mapper.search("colo")
for h in hits:
    print(h.cell_line_name, h.lineage)

# Filter by lineage or disease
lung_cells = mapper.by_lineage("Lung")
melanomas = mapper.by_disease("Melanoma")
```

## Data sources

The mapping table is built by merging:

| Database | ID Type | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| [DepMap](https://depmap.org) | ACH-XXXXXX | `ACH-000024` |
| [GDSC / COSMIC](https://cancer.sanger.ac.uk/cosmic) | Numeric | `905952` |
| [Sanger Cell Model Passports](https://cellmodelpassports.sanger.ac.uk) | SIDMXXXXXX | `SIDM000218` |

The bundled data includes **100+ commonly used cell lines** with full cross-references. To pull the latest complete dataset (~1,800+ cell lines), run:

```bash
pip install cell-id-mapper[update]       # installs requests, pandas
python scripts/update_mappings.py
```

## Project structure

```
cell-id-mapper/
├── src/cell_id_mapper/
│   ├── __init__.py          # Package entry point
│   ├── mapper.py            # Core CellLineMapper class
│   ├── cli.py               # Command-line interface
│   └── data/
│       └── mappings.csv     # Bundled mapping table
├── scripts/
│   └── update_mappings.py   # Fetch latest data from DepMap & GDSC
├── tests/
│   └── test_mapper.py       # Pytest test suite
├── pyproject.toml
├── LICENSE
└── README.md
```

## Requirements

